headline: SMCI Q4 Deep Dive: AI Demand Drives Growth, Margins Under Pressure Amid Customer Shifts
summary: Server solutions provider Super Micro (NASDAQ:SMCI) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 123% year on year to $12.68 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($12.3 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 20.5% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.69 per share was 41.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
